Package HashMap

Class HashMap<K,V>

java.lang.Object
HashMap.HashMap<K,V>
public class HashMap<K,V> extends Object
This is Hash Map data structure . It uses generic data type and hashing function to convert given key into index of given capacity. Separate chaining is used to minimize the colliding. It's implemented using ArrayList data structure.
HashMap<K, V> mp = HashMap<K, V>();

  • Method Details

    • insert

      public void insert(K k, V v)
      Inserting Key and value into Hash Table. The average time complexity of inserting operation will be O(1) If the key is already present then it will update the value with new given value.
      HashMap<Integer, Integer> mp = new HashMap<>(); mp.insert(1, 12);
      Parameters:
      k - : key
      v - : value
